h: Anglicized form of <b>Ó Béara</b>. See   Berry   and   O'Berry  .","Americanized form of Swiss German   Bieri  ."]},{"name":"Berrie","meanings":["Scottish:","(Glasgow): from Middle English or Older Scots <i>(atte) beri</i> ‘(at the) manor house’, see   Berry  .","variant   Barrie  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":36,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Berry was born about 1419, in Berrynarbor, Devon, England, his father, John Berry, was 31 and his mother, Elizabeth, was 31. He married Elizabeth Filleigh about 1440, in Berrynarbor, Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1470, in his hometown, at the age of 53."},"et":{"about 1419–about 1470":"umbes 1419–umbes 1470","1419–1470":"1419–1470","1427–1450":"1427–1450","1441–1493":"1441–1493","1390–1433":"1390–1433","1390–1419":"1390–1419","about 1470":"umbes 1470","1450":"1450","1493":"1493","1470":"1470","1390":"1390","about 1419":"umbes 1419","ABT 1440":"umbes 1440","1455":"1455","1433":"1433","1441":"1441","about 1433":"umbes 1433","1419":"1419","about 1450":"umbes 1450","1427":"1427","Berrynarbor, Devon, England":"Berrynarbor, Devon, England"},"fi":{"about 1419–about 1470":"noin 